The issue with your code is that you are using a for-loop to iterate through the rows of the table, but you are not using the correct index to access the data elements within each row.

Instead of using the index `index++` to access the data elements, you should be using the `Iterator` returned by the `select` method to iterate through the elements in each row.

Here's the updated code:
```java
import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.List;
import java.io.IOException;
import org.jsoup.*;
import org.jsoup.nodes.Document;
import org.jsoup.nodes.Element;
import org.jsoup.select.Elements;

public class MainClass {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException {
        Document doc = Jsoup.connect("http://www.myfxbook.com/forex-market/currencies/GBPUSD-historical-data").get();
        Element table = doc.getElementById("symbolMarket");
        List<Entry> entries = new ArrayList<Entry>();
        for(Element row : table.select("tr")){
            Iterator<Element> iterator = row.getElementsByClass("data").iterator();
            while(iterator.hasNext()) {
                Entry tableEntry = new Entry();
                Element dataElement = iterator.next();
                tableEntry.setDate(dataElement.text());
                tableEntry.setOpen(dataElement.next().text());
                tableEntry.setHigh(dataElement.next().text());
                tableEntry.setLow(dataElement.next().text());
                tableEntry.setClose(dataElement.next().text());
                tableEntry.setChangePips(dataElement.next().text());
                tableEntry.setChangePercent(dataElement.next().text());
                entries.add(tableEntry);
            }
        }
        for(Entry entry : entries) {
            System.out.println(entry.getDate() + " " + entry.getOpen() + " " + entry.getHigh() + " " + entry.getLow() + " " + entry.getClose() + " " + entry.getChangePips() + " " + entry.getChangePercent());
        }
    }
}
```
This code uses the `Iterator` returned by the `select` method to iterate through the elements in each row, and it uses the `next` method to access the data elements within each row. It also adds each `Entry` object to a list and then prints out the data for each entry in the list.
